name: Psychological Erotica Gold Frame
description:
When the dreams first began to go through, I knew something was off about the whole thing but it just felt so right. I'd been so caught up in the enchanting way he spoke that I didn't care that the world seemed off. He was relaxed, a little bit of stubble covered his cheeks and he looked as if he hadn't slept in days, but he still had that dimpled smile that made him look so attractive along with such a beautiful cut body… I couldn’t help myself but go through and have fun with him.
 
The more the dreams occurred though, the more the dreamworld kept on turning like something I can’t properly describe in words.  The world that appeared through my dreams looked as if they had been painted by a graffiti artist, using one of those crazy markers. His body began to look as if it were made of different colors and shapes just like the world was. Every shade of black began to be drawn directly on his skin, some looked detailed and others were just squiggles and scribbles.
 
Despite this, he came up to me, slowly reached out extending his hand, and gazed directly into my eyes. With a very smooth yet firm voice, he told me "Don't worry at all, we're not going anywhere."

—---

The Gallery Gehenna Project is a daily art project where there are multiple frames for each individual artwork, each with different types of rarity applied. Gold frames have the lowest mint rate of the initial 3. All artworks will be compatible within the Gallery Gehenna Game with each artwork unlocking a playable story segment.
